---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import Octocat from "../../components/Octocat.astro";

import githubsvg from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/brands/github.svg?raw";
import npmsvg from "@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/svgs/brands/npm.svg?raw";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Srcery Theme - Various resources"
  description="Look up various Srcery resources, here lives everything that is not a theme"
>
  <Octocat />
  <div class="flex grow justify-center p-4">
    <main class="flex max-w-[448px] min-w-0 flex-col items-center sm:max-w-[780px]">
      <Header activePage="resources" />
      <section class="w-full">
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="mb-3 text-center text-xl uppercase sm:text-left">
            Resources
          </h2>
          <p class="text-justify">
            Here are collected miscellaneous Srcery resources. In addition to
            themes, Srcery has some tools and packages to assist in creating new
            themes, or things that didn't fit anywhere else.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="mb-3 text-center uppercase sm:text-left">Palette</h3>
          <p id="version-block" class="mb-4 hidden">
            <span class="">Latest version:</span>
            <a
              id="version-link"
              href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@srcery-colors/srcery-palette"
              class="link"
            ></a>
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4">
            In an attempt to create a single source of truth concerning the
            palette used in various themes, a npm package was created that
            contains a JSON with all color information.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4">
            It isn't used in every project, but every change to the palette will
            happen there first, and will produce a new version of this package
            going forward.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Install using this command or check out the links below:
          </p>
          <code class="code"> npm i @srcery-colors/srcery-palette </code>
          <ul class="">
            <li class="mb-2 flex items-center">
              <div class="list-dot"></div>
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="flex items-center link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-palette"
              >
                <div class="mr-2 w-5 svg" set:html={githubsvg} />
                GitHub repository
              </a>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center">
              <div class="list-dot"></div>
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="flex items-center link"
                href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@srcery-colors/srcery-palette"
              >
                <div class="mr-2 w-8 svg" set:html={npmsvg} />
                <div>
                  <span class="mr-1">npm package</span>
                  <span id="version-inline" class="hidden"
                    >(<strong id="version-inline-text"></strong>)</span
                  >
                </div>
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-center text-xl uppercase sm:text-left">
            Web assets
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Aside from the palette itself, here are some useful web assets.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-web/tree/master/tailwind"
              >
                Tailwind config
              </a>
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-web/tree/master/tridactyl"
                >Tridactyl theme</a
              >
              <span class="text-sm text-white"
                >- This will be moved to a new repo soon</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-web/tree/master/userstyles"
                >User styles</a
              >
              <span class="text-sm text-white"
                >- Using stylish extension for example</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-web/tree/master/palette"
                >Palette</a
              >
              <span class="text-sm text-white"
                >this is deprecated for the palette above, kept for
                compatibility</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-center text-xl uppercase sm:text-left">
            Graphic assets
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            We keep graphic assets in a separate repo so not to inflate the size
            of each theme. Source for SVGs of various assets are kept in the
            <code class="inline-code">src</code> folder.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4">
            If you are looking for icons, logo, screenshots, etcetera, this is
            the place.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-assets"
              >
                GitHub repository
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-center text-xl uppercase sm:text-left">
            Miscellaneous
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Here are some miscellaneous projects that don't really fit anywhere
            else. Mostly experiments and and other bits and bobs.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery.sh"
                >Srcery Website</a
              >
              <span class="text-sm text-white">- Source code for this site</span>
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-convert"
                >Srcery Convert</a
              >
              <span class="text-sm text-white"
                >- Rust program to convert an input image palette to Srcery
                colors, your mileage may vary</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="mb-2">
              <a
                target="_blank"
                class="link"
                href="https://github.com/srcery-colors/srcery-misc"
                >Srcery Miscellaneous</a
              >
              <span class="text-sm text-white"
                >- Mostly unused files in here</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  fetch("https://registry.npmjs.org/@srcery-colors/srcery-palette")
    .then((res) => res.json())
    .then((json) => {
      const version = json?.["dist-tags"]?.latest;
      if (!version) return;

      const link = document.getElementById("version-link") as HTMLAnchorElement;
      link.textContent = version;
      document.getElementById("version-block")!.classList.remove("hidden");

      const inlineText = document.getElementById("version-inline-text")!;
      inlineText.textContent = version;
      document.getElementById("version-inline")!.classList.remove("hidden");
    });
</script>

